Regular Expression


A rule written in code that checks whether text follows a specific pattern.

Example:
A simple regex might check:

- Has text before @
- Has @
- Has text after @ 
- Has a dot in the domain

In code, it might look like something ugly like:
^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$

Just understand the concerp do NOT memorize this.

Regex = pattern matching tool.


Why is Regex used for email?

Because instead of manualy checking every single condition set regex makes it easier by knocking out patterns which is 
efficient, compact, and common.